    {
      "id": 405,
      "question_id": 120,
      "step_order": 10,
      "step_title": "1. Can I view sales from 'Online' and 'Offline' channels together?",
      "content": "<p><em style=\"background-color: rgba(254, 237, 175, 0.5); color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">Yes. The &#39;Sales Over Time&#39; report combines all your sales data (POS, Beep Delivery, QR Order &amp; Pay) into one view by default.</em></p>",
      "image_url": null,
      "video_url": null,
      "block_type": "step",
      "images": []
    },
    {
      "id": 406,
      "question_id": 120,
      "step_order": 11,
      "step_title": "2. Can I see the profit margin for my sales?",
      "content": "<p><em style=\"background-color: rgba(254, 237, 175, 0.5); color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">Yes. In the &#39;Sales Over Time&#39; report, you can view your Gross Profit (GP%). You can switch the chart view to show &#39;GP%&#39; or look at the data table below the chart.</em></p>",
      "image_url": null,
      "video_url": null,
      "block_type": "step",
      "images": []
    },
    {
      "id": 407,
      "question_id": 120,
      "step_order": 12,
      "step_title": "3. Can I filter these reports by specific stores?",
      "content": "<p><em style=\"background-color: rgba(254, 237, 175, 0.5); color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">Yes. Almost all reports have a &#39;Filters&#39; button that allows you to view data for a specific store branch if you have multiple locations.</em></p>",
      "image_url": null,
      "video_url": null,
      "block_type": "step",
      "images": []
    },
    {
